        <p>Here's something most nutrition apps won't tell you: 80% of what you eat comes from about 20% of foods. Most men over 40 eat the same 8–12 foods in regular rotation — chicken breast, eggs, Greek yogurt, cottage cheese, a protein shake, some fish, some beef. Week after week, the core list barely changes.</p>
        <p>That's not a failure of dietary variety. It's human nature. We're creatures of habit, especially around food. And it means you don't need a searchable database of tens of thousands of foods to track your protein accurately. You need your actual foods — the ones you eat — to be fast and easy to log.</p>
        <p>The problem isn't variety. It's that those foods aren't adding up to enough protein.</p>
        <p>SnapProtein's 4-slot shortcut design was intentional. Not a limitation — a decision. Your most important protein sources live one tap away. That's the whole system. The foods you eat every week shouldn't require a search.</p>

